attributes.text:
@dev Function allows all users to break staking instance and withdraw
 all eth deposited for staking.

earlyWithdraw().details: Breaks staking instance for users with a duration tier higher than the default of 5. A relative amount of tokens reserved are sent to the user based on time staked.

emergencyWithdraw().details: Function allows all users to break staking instance and withdraw all eth deposited for staking.

getLotteryContract().details: Getter function to pull current lottery address

getStakingStatus().details: Getter function to pull staking status on and off.

getTierInformation(uint256,uint256).details: Getter function pulls current tier information.

params._amount: amount value sent in ETH used to access tier combination.
params._timeTier: key tier time value used to access tier combination.

returns._0: Returns the interest under time and amount tier combination, amount of stakers avaliable. and the tierDuration or period staked in EPOCH.

getTokenReserve(address).details: Getter function to pull information for avaliable token amount in reserves

getTokenReturn(uint256,uint256,address).details: Function sends an estimation of how many tokens user is owed

params._amount: Amount of ETH send by the user

getTokenSupport().details: Getter function to pull info on support for other tokens.

getUser(address).details: Getter function to pull information from the user.

getUserBalance(address,address).details: Getter function to pull avaliable tokens ready to withdraw from reserves

lotteryWinner(address).details: Getter function to pull information on lottery winner

returns._0: if user has a multiplier ready to be reedemed

setLotteryContract(address).details: Setter function to change the contract address for the lottery connected to staking.

params._lotteryAddress: address of lottery contract picking winners.

setStakingStatus(bool).details: Setter function to turn staking status on and off.

setStakingTermination(bool).details: Function terminates all staking instances and allows early balance withdrewal

params._bool: true terminates all contract instances and allows users to withdraw

setTierInformation(uint256,uint256,uint2.details: Setter function to modify interests based on time and amount

params._amountTier: key tier amount value used to access tier combination.
params._tierDuration: new tier duration to be modified.
params._timeTier: key tier time value used to access tier combination.

setTokenSupport(bool).details: Setter function to turn support for other tokens.

params._bool: true turns on other token support for staking reward, false off

stakeEth(uint32,address).details: Function stakes ethereum based on the user's desired duration and token of reward

params._timeStakedTier: intended duration of their desired staking period
params._tokenAddress: token address rewarded to user staking CBLT used as default during launch

tokenReserveDeposit(uint256,address).details: Function handles token deposit for treasury to track

withdrawEth(uint256).details: Function sends a specified amount of ETH from the users balance back to the user

withdrawFees(uint256).details: transfers funds to an approved contract

withdrawStaking(uint256,address).details: Function transfer an amount of desired cblt tokens from the user's token reward wallet.

params._amount: amount of token rewarded sent to the user's wallet
params._withdrawTokenAddress: token address of token being withdrawn

Lottery.details: Address of lottery contract in charge of executing LotteryWinner function

borrowingPool.details: Variable displays information on ETH staked in the treasury for time tiers 4 and 5.

lotteryBook.details: Mapping with key value uint (lottery ticket) leads to the information on ticket amount and time tier for the user to redeem his reward staking.

multipleTokenSupport.details: Bool switch turns support for other tokens as reward outside of CBLT.

oracleAddress.details: CobaltLend oracle for scoring and CBLT price

rewardWallet.details: Mapping with key value address (user address) leads to submapping with key value address (token address) to pull the current balance rewarded to that user in the tokens

stakingRewardRate.details: Nested mappings with key value uint (time tier) leads to submapping with key value uint (amount tier) that leads the crossTier combination to pull the combination's interest amount of stakers avaliable and the tier duration used to calculate due date period.

stakingStatus.details: Variable to turn staking off and on.

terminateStaking.details: Bool switch for all staking instance terminations

tierMax.details: Variable displaying the maximum time tier supported.

token.details: storing CBLT token in ERC20 type

tokenReserve.details: Mapping with key value address (token address) leads the current reserves avaliable for tokens being currently offered to stake on.

userBook.details: Mapping with key value address(the user's address) leads to the struct with the user's staking and lottery information.

lottery(address[]).notice: Only an allowed address will be able to execute this function

newFlatFee(uint256).notice: This action can only be perform under dev vote.

setLotteryContract(address).notice: This action can only be perform under dev vote.

setStakingStatus(bool).notice: This action can only be perform under dev vote.

setStakingTermination(bool).notice: This action can only be perform under dev vote.

setTierInformation(uint256,uint256,uint2.notice: Function is used to modify existing tiers or create new tiers if new tier key values are passed, creating new tier combinations.If time tier used is higher than current tier max, new tier combination was just created and tierMax should change to new capThis action can only be perform under dev vote

setTokenSupport(bool).notice: This action can only be perform under dev vote.

stakeEth(uint32,address).notice: Modifier tokenIsCBLT checks if support for other tokens as reward is turned on.

withdrawEth(uint256).notice: Function also allocates final amount tokens owed into users reward wallet if this hasnt ocurred already

withdrawStaking(uint256,address).notice: Function also calculates any running token balance reserved and deposits it on the user's reward wallet
